Question 1
Which of the following is true of a ViewGroup in Android Studio?

0 / 1 point

A ViewGroup represents a rectangular area of the screen and is used for
displaying information.


A ViewGroup defines layout in which views will be arranged on the Android screen.


A ViewGroup is a special view that can contain one or more other views.

Correct
Correct. ViewGroup is a special use of the view class because it can contain one or more other views.

