Question 7
Which built-in package in Android Studio is used to locate resources, such as a file you want a video player app to play?

1 / 1 point

MediaController


URI


VideoView

Correct
That's correct. URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) is a built-in package that allows you to reference the location of a particular resource, whether it is in your application folder or on the user's device. 

